      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "From a strict realist or consequentialist perspective, creating a larger, more destructive security vacuum constitutes an objective strategic failure. If the long-term geopolitical costs—such as fueled migration and terrorism—outweigh any short-term humanitarian gains, the intervention failed its broader strategic mission. This view prioritizes macroscopic stability over localized immediate relief, making the negative multipliers the definitive measure of failure.",
